The Katsina State Police Command has arrested 25-year-old Musa Shamsudin, for aiding and providing medical services to bandits in Katsina State. The command’s spokesman, Gambo Isah, disclosed this to journalists on Wednesday while parading some hoodlums arrested for various offences from across the state. The Police PRO said in the course of investigation some quantity of drugs were recovered from the suspect, adding that investigation was ongoing on the matter. “A fake medical personnel, Musa Shamsudin, ‘M’, aged 25yrs, an indigene of Kogi State but residing at Kankara was suspected of always going into the forest to treat sick and wounded bandits. “In the course of investigation, some quantities of drugs were recovered in his possession. He was alleged to have disappeared from Kankara on the day in which Kankara schoolboys were abducted by bandits and later resurfaced. Investigation is ongoing,” the police spokesman said.